# AMR-GigaWord 200k

# ::id 0 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok no information linking people or organizations in south africa to last week 's terrorist attacks in the united states has been uncovered , government officials said friday .
# ::alignments
(s / say-01
      :ARG0 (p / person
            :ARG0-of (h / have-org-role-91
                  :ARG1 (g / government-organization
                        :ARG0-of (g2 / govern-01))
                  :ARG2 (o / official)))
      :ARG1 (u / uncover-01
            :polarity -
            :ARG1 (ii / information
                  :ARG3-of (l / link-01
                        :ARG1 (o2 / or
                              :op1 p)
                        :op2 (o3 / organization)
                        :location (w / world-region
                              :name (n / name
                                    :op1 "South"
                                    :op2 "Africa")))
                  :ARG2 (a / attack-01
                        :ARG0 (t / terrorist)
                        :location (c / country
                              :name (n2 / name
                                    :op1 "United"
                                    :op2 "States"))
                        :time (w2 / week
                              :mod (l2 / last)))))
      :time (d / date-entity
            :weekday (f / friday)))

# ::id 1 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok the plenary session of the second round of burundi talks was adjourned again following a request from the burundian government delegation .
# ::alignments
(a / adjourn-01
      :ARG1 (s / session
            :mod (p / plenary)
            :subevent-of (r / round
                  :ord (o / ordinal-entity
                        :value 2)
                  :subevent-of (t / talk-01
                        :ARG0 (c / country
                              :name (n / name
                                    :op1 "Burundia")))))
      :ARG1-of (f / follow-01
            :ARG2 (r2 / request-01
                  :ARG0 (d / delegation
                        :mod (g / government-organization
                              :ARG0-of (g2 / govern-01
                                    :ARG1 c)))))
      :mod (a2 / again))

# ::id 2 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

                  :op1 "IBM"))

            :ARG0 c
            :ARG1 (r / responsible-03
                  :ARG0 c
                  :ARG1 (l / lead-02
                        :ARG0 c
                        :ARG1 (u / unit
                              :mod (b / big)
                              :mod (s2 / service)
                              :poss c)))
            :ARG2 (r2 / reorganize-01
                  :ARG0 c
                  :ARG1 (m / manage-01)))
      :time (d / date-entity
            :weekday (t / tuesday)))

      :time (d / date-entity
            :weekday (t2 / tuesday))
      :ARG0-of (s / set-02
            :ARG1 (r / roadblock
                  :ARG1-of (m2 / major-02))

                                    :op1 "South"
                                    :op2 "Pacific"))
                        :mod (p / past
                              :op1 (a / and
                                    :op1 (g2 / game
                                          :name (n3 / name
                                                :op1 "Lb-fespic"))
                                    :op2 (g3 / game
                                          :mod w
                                          :mod (f / far))))
                        :beneficiary (p2 / person
                              :ARG1-of (d2 / disable-01))))
            :ARG1 (s / start-01
                  :ARG1 g
                  :ARG1-of (f2 / fly-01))
            :ARG0-of s
            :ARG2 (t / take-01
                  :ARG1 (m / medal
                        :mod (g4 / gold)
                        :ARG1-of (o / offer-01
                              :time (d3 / day
                                    :ord (o2 / ordinal-entity
                                          :value 1)
                                    :time-of (c2 / compete-01)))))
            :ARG0-of t
            :location (h / here)))
